<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>at the same time • in the same time</xh5><p> <i>at the same time—</i>1. in addition; as well: The method reduced the cost of processing information and <u>at the same time</u> accelerated the speed of producing data. 2. at the same moment; simultaneously: The same stock may be quoted <u>at the same time</u> in the exchange markets of distant places. 3. nevertheless <i>(is used to express reservation):</i> That’s all fine and well, but <u>at the same time</u> it seems increasingly unlikely that we will achieve these goals.</p><p><i>in the same time—</i>taking the same amount of time: This explains why a planet travels from point A to point B <u>in the same time</u> that it takes to cover the much shorter span between C and D.</p> </entry>
